author: NHHMS
title: Kehlani Vows to Love Who She Wants on New Song 'Undercover'
text:
http://www.billboard.com/files/styles/promo_225/public/media/Kehlani-press-cr-atlantic-records-billboard-1548.jpg 
Kehlani sets her latest love note loose with “Undercover.” 
Here, the Bay Area songstress gives a nod to Akon ’s upbeat number “Don’t Matter” with the song’s first line. Backed by a sweet acoustic guitar, the Charlie Heat-produced track finds the singer vowing to love who she wants, no matter what “they” think with lyrics like “One way or another/ I’mma love you/ Slidin’ under covers, undercover/ They don’t wanna see us happy but we say f— it.” 
“Undercover” is off Kehlani’s upcoming album SweetSexySavage , due Jan. 27. Her debut will include previously released tracks “CRZY,”“Advice” and “Distraction.” The songstress is also heading out on a world tour in February. 
Listen to “Undercover” and check out the tour dates below. SSS World Tour Kicks off in February! Openers: @ellamai @jahkoy @bbnoodz , tickets on sale Wednesday!!! See you there!! pic.twitter.com/k4DJiqb17G
